<ce:para>We obtain the following characterization of Q-polynomial distance-regular graphs. Let Γ denote a distance-regular graph with diameter d≥3. Let E denote a minimal idempotent of Γ which is not the trivial idempotent E0. Let {θi*}i=0d denote the dual eigenvalue sequence for E. We show that E is Q-polynomial if and only if (i) the entry-wise product E°E is a linear combination of E0, E, and at most one other minimal idempotent of Γ; (ii) there exists a complex scalar β such that θi*1-βΓi*+θi+1* is independent of i for 1≤i≤d-1; (iii) θi*≠θ0* for 1≤i≤d. © 2010 Elsevier Inc.</ce:para>
